# BetLab Backend

- Backend runtime is Node.js + Express (CommonJS).
- Server entrypoint is `backend/src/server.js`.
- Express app setup belongs in `backend/src/app.js`.
- Maintain backend process docs in `docs/backend-process.md`.

# Routing Conventions

- Mount all API endpoints under `/api`.
- Keep route modules in `backend/src/routes`.
- Keep a simple health endpoint at `/api/health`.

# Middleware Conventions

- Keep middleware in `backend/src/middleware`.
- Use centralized not-found and error-handler middleware.
- Return JSON errors using `{ ok: false, error: "<message>" }`.
- Log unexpected 5xx errors in the centralized error handler.

# Environment Conventions

- Keep local environment template in `backend/.env.example`.
- Expected vars:
  - `PORT`
  - `CORS_ORIGIN`
  - `MONGO_DB_URI` (or `mongo_db_uri`)
  - `BASKETBALL_MODEL_RESULTS_DIR` (optional override)
  - `BASKETBALL_MODEL_STATS_DIR` (optional override)

# Round Leader Projection Conventions

- PGA schedule picker data is cached in `backend/data/round-leader-projection-events.json`.
- Read cached schedule events via `GET /api/tools/round-leader-projection/events`.
- Refresh and overwrite cached schedule events via `POST /api/tools/round-leader-projection/events/refresh`.
- Projection requests accept `selectedStats` so users can define custom stat groups.
- Projection requests accept `projectionModel` (`standard` or `blended`); `standard` preserves full Par + SG stacking, while `blended` keeps course baseline and applies weighted skill adjustments (`65%` Par, `35%` SG when both families are selected).
- Supported stat keys: `course_hole_model`, `par3_scoring_avg`, `par4_scoring_avg`, `par5_scoring_avg`, `sg_total`, `sg_t2g`, `sg_ott`, `sg_app`, `sg_arg`, `sg_putt`, `recent_form_l20`.
- If `sg_total` is selected, reject any payload that includes other SG keys to avoid redundant SG stacking.
- If `sg_t2g` is selected, reject payloads that also include its overlapping components (`sg_ott`, `sg_app`, `sg_arg`); `sg_putt` can still pair with `sg_t2g`.
- Allocate SG component adjustments by remaining-hole context while preserving each selected SG stat's per-round edge: `sg_ott` applies only to par 4/5 holes, `sg_app` is weighted more heavily on par 3s, and `sg_total`, `sg_t2g`, `sg_arg`, and `sg_putt` distribute broadly across holes.
- If Tourcast GraphQL endpoint discovery fails, fall back to hole-level scoring data from `course-stats` instead of failing the request.
- Cache stat snapshots by `tournamentId + currentRound + sorted(selectedStats)` in `backend/data/round-leader-projection-stats-cache.json`.
- Include SG parser/cache versioning in the stat snapshot cache key so parsing fixes, such as DataGolf sentinel handling, do not reuse stale poisoned cached field means.
- Source SG stats from latest `backend/data/YYYY-MM-DD-strokes-gained.csv` instead of PGA SG stat pages.
- SG player mapping should tolerate ordering/punctuation differences and minor name variations.
- Source recent-form stats from latest `backend/data/dg_group_trending_table-*.csv` unless the request includes an uploaded Recent Form CSV.
- Recent Form CSV validation requires `player_name`, `true_sg_l20`, and `vs_baseline_l20`; projections use `vs_baseline_l20` as `recent_form_l20`.
- Apply `recent_form_l20` as a conservative recent-form overlay after Par/SG blending, using the request `recentFormWeight` (`0.30` default, clamped `0`-`1`) prorated by remaining holes; do not include it inside the Par/SG blended model weights.
- Projection payload player rows include win/tie probabilities (`winSoloProbability`, `tieForLeadProbability`) plus tie-splitting share probability fields and FV fields (`fairValueYesProbability`, `fairValueYesCents`) from Monte Carlo simulation.
- Projection payload should include scope datasets in `projectionScopes` for `round` and `tournament`, with `players` retaining round-scope compatibility; the frontend derives `Group Winner` from tournament-scope rows.
- Include per-player `scoreStdDev` in projected rows so frontend group-winner simulations can reuse backend score uncertainty without re-scraping.
- Include tournament progress metadata (`currentRound`, `totalRounds`, `roundsRemainingAfterCurrent`) so frontend can display days/rounds remaining.
- Tournament-scope tie resolution should model playoff single-winner outcomes with SG-weighted softmax allocation (fallback to equal split if SG signal is unavailable).
- Tournament-scope player rows should include `top20/top10/top5` probabilities using dead-heat settlement shares when ties cross a top-finish cutoff (for example, tie for 10th splits top-10 payout share).
- Projection requests can include optional `weatherOverrides` (`enabled`, `amWaveAdjustmentPerRound`, `pmWaveAdjustmentPerRound`, `windVolatilityMultiplier`); apply these only to round-scope mean/variance and never to tournament-scope projections.
- Projection requests can include per-player `statOverrides` (par averages and SG keys) and `scoreOverrides` (`totalScoreNumber`, `roundScoreNumber`, `completedHoles`), and player responses should expose effective input metadata (`playerStatInputs`, `playerScoreInputs`) including `baselineValue` so frontend can distinguish meaningful manual overrides from unchanged pre-filled values.
- Always populate `playerStatInputs` for all editable projection stat keys (par + SG) so frontend exports/edit flows have a complete per-player stat payload regardless selected stats.
- Player responses should expose `missingProjectionStats`/`missingProjectionStatKeys` for selected Par/SG stats that fall back to field mean or zero values, so the frontend can warn when any stat used in the projection is missing.
- For pre-tournament/not-started players with missing live totals, treat projection baseline score as `E` (0) while preserving raw feed display values.
- For upcoming tournaments before leaderboard rows exist, build pre-tournament projection rows from the PGA `tcotrPlayerStatus` field list, resolve course metadata from tournament/course-stats payloads, and use even-par hole baselines until live scoring averages are available.
- If PGA feed marks a player as `ACTIVE` but score fields are blank and a tee time exists, infer `not started` for projection baseline and score display purposes.
- For `BETWEEN_ROUNDS` players with a scheduled tee time but no current-round score/thru, show tee time in score display and infer weather wave from tee time; if active players lose tee-time in feed, infer weather wave from nearest group-number tee-time sample.
- Projection requests can include optional `uploadedSgCsv` payloads (`fileName`, `content`) to override the default backend SG CSV source for that request.
- Projection requests can include optional `uploadedRecentFormCsv` payloads (`fileName`, `content`) to override the default backend Recent Form CSV source for that request.
- Keep Express JSON body limit high enough for combined projection CSV upload payloads, currently `5mb` in `backend/src/app.js`.
- Validate uploaded SG CSV structure via `POST /api/tools/round-leader-projection/validate-sg-csv`; accept either BetLab prediction columns (`player_name`, `sg_total_pred`, `sg_ott_pred`, `sg_app_pred`, `sg_arg_pred`, `sg_putt_pred`) or DataGolf skill-rating columns (`player_name`, `total_true`, `ott_true`, `app_true`, `arg_true`, `putt_true`, with `t2g_true` optional because it can be derived).
- Validate uploaded Recent Form CSV structure via `POST /api/tools/round-leader-projection/validate-recent-form-csv`.
- Treat DataGolf SG sentinel values like `-9999` as missing, not real SG values; missing SG components should fall back to field means instead of contaminating field averages.
